name: line_break_ascii_lf
description: |
  This baseline separates "A" and "B" with ASCII LINE FEED (U+000A). It pairs
  with Unicode line-boundary characters that may render similarly but are not
  recognized by APIs, regular expressions, protocols, or file readers that
  only handle LF or CRLF.

  Unicode Standard Annex #14 defines line-break classes:
  https://www.unicode.org/reports/tr14/
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: utf8
unicode-meta:
  code-units: 3
  code-points: 3
  scalar-values: 3
  legacy-grapheme-clusters: 3
  extended-grapheme-clusters: 3
pair:
  - with: next-line.input
    hint: not-equal
  - with: line-separator.input
    hint: not-equal
  - with: paragraph-separator.input
    hint: not-equal
tags:
  - "utf8"
  - "unicode"
  - "line-separators"
  - "baseline"
---
A
B
